# Zoom Integration Configuration
# 
# These variables enable NAVI to sync Zoom meeting transcripts into conversational memory.
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to Zoom App Marketplace: https://marketplace.zoom.us/
# 2. Click "Develop" → "Build App"
# 3. Choose "Server-to-Server OAuth" app type
# 4. Fill in app name and basic information
# 5. On the "App Credentials" page, note:
#    - Account ID
#    - Client ID
#    - Client Secret
# 6. Add the following scopes under "Scopes":
#    - cloud_recording:read:list_user_recordings:admin (to list recordings)
#    - cloud_recording:read:list_recording_files:admin (to download transcripts)
# 7. Activate the app
# 8. Copy these values to your .env file

# Zoom Account ID (from App Credentials page)
AEP_ZOOM_ACCOUNT_ID=your-zoom-account-id-here

# Zoom Client ID (from App Credentials page)
AEP_ZOOM_CLIENT_ID=your-zoom-client-id-here

# Zoom Client Secret (from App Credentials page)
AEP_ZOOM_CLIENT_SECRET=your-zoom-client-secret-here

# Default Zoom user to pull recordings for (email or "me")
# Can be overridden per request
AEP_ZOOM_USER_EMAIL=your.email@company.com

# Notes:
# - Requires Zoom Pro, Business, or Enterprise account with cloud recording enabled
# - Transcripts must be enabled in Zoom settings (Account → Recording → Cloud recording → Advanced → Audio transcript)
# - Only meetings with available transcripts will be ingested
